org.sikuli.script

Class ObserverCallBack

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sikuli.script.ObserverCallBack
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.EventListener

    public class ObserverCallBack
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.EventListener
    Use this class to implement call back methods for the Region observers onAppear, onVanish and onChange.
    by overriding the respective method appeared, vanished or changed 
     example:
 aRegion.onAppear(anImageOrPattern,
   new ObserverCallBack() {
     appeared(ObserveEvent e) {
       // do something
     }
   }
 );
    when the image appears, your above call back appeared() will be called
    see ObserveEvent about the features available in the callback function
